=begin
   This script creates a dedicated window to display all signature verbs, race specific verbs, and roleplay verbs available to the player.
   Race specific verbs are automatically loaded for the players race according to Lich.
   Roleplay verbs are any verb that performs an action seen by others by using VERB or VERB YOU.
   And example of this is NOD and NOD WYROM.
   
   Features:
   - Automatically parses the output of the SIGNATURE and VERB LIST LETTER(a-z) commands and populates a dynamic Wrayth window with all signature verbs known by the player as well as all verbs in the game with VERB INFO.
   - Displays an alphabetical clickable list of all signature verbs and regular verbs that shows SIGNATURE VIEW or a preview of each verb.
   - Some verbs can be executed with the verb only by clicking ( ! ).
   - Some verbs can be excuted with the VERB YOURNAMEHERE by clicking (S).
   - Tags signature verbs that require a player target with (T).
   - Allows the player to customize the list by clicking an [ X ] to hide signature or regular verbs.
   - Hidden verbs are populated at the very bottom of the window and can be clicked to make them unhidden.
   - Players can now load a profile using ;send load profilename that overrides the hidden verbs list.
   - You can also save a custom profile using ;send save profile_name which stores the current visible regular verbs.
   - A reverse lookup window is available by typing ;send reverse in game.
   - ;send help for the help menu.
   - ;send regular to enable or disable regular verbs in the window.
   - ;send race to enable or disable race verbs in the window.
   - ;send hidden to enable or disable hidden verbs in the window.
   
   Updates:
   - Giantman race specific verbs added for pound.
   - Dwarf race specific verbs added for belch, grunt, and swear.
   - Aelotoi race specific verbs added for blink, bow, flap, flutter, fold, preen, snap wings, stare, twitch, wave wings.
   - Human race specific verbs added for bow and shrug.
   - Elf race specific verbs added for belch and disdain.
   
   Tips:
   - Add these lines to Wrayth Text Highlights and color them black.
   [exec1:
   --- Lich: exec1 has exited.
   --- Lich: exec1 active.
   
author: Phocosoen, ChatGPT
contributors: Tysong, Nisgui
tags: wrayth, frontend, mod, window, signature, emote, verb
version: 1.4.0
=end

